<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e828f637e91f7d986b7a79574dc0c45a?s=50"></div><header><strong>&quot;where&quot; on a switch case with multiple items is misleading</strong> from <string>Amir Michail</string> &lt;a.michail at me.com&gt;<p>March 11, 2016 at 07:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>Consider:<br></p><p>switch x { <br>	case a, b where …: ...<br>}<br></p><p>this currently means:<br></p><p>switch x { <br>	case a where true, b where …: ...<br>}<br></p><p>Most people would probably think the “where&quot; applies to both a and b.<br></p><p>To avoid this confusion, maybe if “where&quot; is used for one item then it should be required for all items in that case?<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
